<subSubSection id="94A154849A034345FF57CF1EFEB83232" pageId="7" pageNumber="1242" type="description">
<paragraph id="DC04070F9A034345FF57CF1EFEB83232" blockId="7.[178,1085,523,634]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1242">
C o m m e n t: 
<taxonomicName id="1BBB7C8C9A034345FE8DCF1EFE203269" authorityName="BERNHAUER" authorityYear="1907" box="[360,486,523,545]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Othius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rosti">
<emphasis id="EECFDB1D9A034345FE8DCF1EFE203269" box="[360,486,523,545]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1242">Othius rosti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the most widespread species in the East Palaearctic region. Its distribution is somewhat more northern than that of 
<taxonomicName id="1BBB7C8C9A034345FC83CF3CFC153275" authorityName="SHARP" authorityYear="1874" box="[870,979,552,574]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Othius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medius">
<emphasis id="EECFDB1D9A034345FC83CF3CFC153275" box="[870,979,552,574]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1242">O. medius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="44801B8A9A034345FC03CF3CFBF63277" box="[998,1072,553,575]" captionStart="Map 4" captionStartId="6.[178,223,1038,1059]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1030]" captionTargetId="figure-230@6.[178,1085,212,1030]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Map 4: Distribution of Othius rosti in the East Palaearctic region, based on examined records (black circles) and one literature record (white circle)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5415937" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5415937/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="1242">Map 4</figureCitation>
). Recently, the species was reported also from 
<collectingCountry id="A4AC479F9A034345FD45CF53FD1A3214" box="[672,732,582,604]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="1242">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="1E7FC9ED9A034345FD0ACF53FCB13214" box="[751,887,582,604]" country="China" name="Heilongjiang" pageId="7" pageNumber="1242">Heilongjiang</collectingRegion>
) for the first time (
<bibRefCitation id="B82A7AFE9A034345FF5CCF71FEB53232" author="WANG Y &amp; TANG L" box="[185,371,611,634]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1242" pagination="80 - 82" refId="ref7509" refString="WANG Y., TANG L. &amp; L. - Z. LI (2012): A new record species [sic] from China, othius rosti [sic] (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Journal of Shanghai Normal University (Natural Sciences) 41 (1): 80 - 82." type="journal article" year="2012">WANG et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
